data.meta_description: King Chulalongkorn (Rama V) of Siam and Tsar Nicholas II of Russia in St. Petersburg, 1897. This was a reciprocal visit by the Siamese King after the then Tsarevich and him met in Bangkok when Nicholas toured the far east. Chulalongkorn's son Chakrabongse remained in St Petersburg, became a Russian officer and eventually married a Russian Ekaterina ‘Katya’ Desnitskaya before they both returned to Bangkok.  Source - The amazing Tatiana Z site
